\
When tapping a load, support two actions:\
1. View Details\
2. Start Receiving\
\
Do not mix load details and scanner work mode together.\
\
RECEIVE LOAD WORK MODE\
\
This is the core workflow.\
\
Steps:\
1. Verify BOL / packing list against scheduled shipment\
2. Confirm packing list\
3. Scan or generate UPC\
4. Enter SKU / part number / item name\
5. Enter quantity\
6. Create label\
7. Mark overage / shortage / damage if needed\
8. Verify totals\
9. Sign off load\
\
Screen should include:\
- Sticky load header\
- Shipment ID\
- Dock door\
- Carrier\
- Status\
- Scanner locked chip\
- Big Scan Item action\
- Generate UPC\
- Add Line Manually\
- Create Label\
- Received inventory line list\
- Exception button\
- Verify Totals\
- Sign Off Load\
\
INVENTORY TAB\
\
Inventory is the center tab.\
\
It is the universal lookup and material action hub.\
